HEADWORD: Sumatra leaf
<hw>Su*ma"tra leaf</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A thin, elastic, uniformly
light-colored tobacco leaf, raised in Sumatra and extensively used for
cigar wrappers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

